<input type="hidden" name="course" value="problemset">
<input type="hidden" name="task" value="1692">
Your task is to construct a minimum-length bit string that contains all possible substrings of length $n$. For example, when $n=2$, the string 00110 is a valid solution, because its substrings of length $2$ are 00, 01, 10 and 11.<br />
<br />
<b id="input">Input</b><br />
<br />
The only input line has an integer $n$.<br />
<br />
<b id="output">Output</b><br />
<br />
Print a minimum-length bit string that contains all substrings of length $n$. You can print any valid solution.<br />
<br />
<b id="constraints">Constraints</b><br />
<ul>
<li>$1 \le n \le 15$<br />
</ul>
<b id="example">Example</b><br />
<br />
Input:<br />
<code>2</code><br />
<br />
Output:<br />
<code>00110</code>    </div>
